      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it's not just about \"fake profiles\"... it's the nuance. it's using my specific way of thinking. i saw a post where it debated a topic exactly how i would've, even bringing up a memory from my childhood that i've never even posted about. it's like it has a map of my mind. if an AI was trained on every single scrap of my data, wouldn't it eventually become indistinguishable from the original person? like, at what point does the simulation become the reality?",
